::Alysia sat in her throne smiling after a wonderful visit from her daughter Aliya. She was finally at peace. Meanwhile. .. . . . .<br>
<br>
<br>
In the Alternate Universe. . . . . .<br>
<br>
<br>
Sapphira sat on her high throne as the empress of the Roman legions in her area of ruling. She smiled down at her son who was sitting before the Gate that opened the portal to the other world. She smiled and ran a hand through her short blonde hair. <br>
<br>
&quot;The Amazons will never suspect us comming my child.&quot;<br>
<br>
The young boy looked to his mother. <br>
&quot;But what if this Wulf boy is stronger than I?&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
She grinned. &quot;Just remember that if he kills you, he kills himself in the process. And that leaves the gate open forever!&quot; She cackled loudly.<br>
<br>
A knock was heard at her chambers.<br>
<br>
&quot;Enter.&quot; She yelled.<br>
<br>
A few Roman women entered the area. &quot;We are ready my leige.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sapphira smiled and looked to them.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now remember, when we enter this world. You each will have another. . .a twin. . a mirror image if you will. Do not kill them or you yourself will be destroyed! But wound them very badly and then lock them up. In time you will heal and then when that happens, my son shall sacrifice the child called Wulf, and we shall remain in the Scynthia Village forever!&quot;<br>
<br>
The other Romans grinned and raised their swords in glory.<br>
<br>
The young boy looked at the portal and raised his hands, he then stood and yelled into the gate. &quot;OPEN!&quot;<br>
<br>
Nothing Happened. ..  .<br>
<br>
