<br>
She growled and flipped up. She didn't want to fight knowing the effect it would have on Dawn. Alysia then turned her eyes towards her son as he came out of the weapon hut holding his own sword in hand. She had a bad feeling that Wulf was what Sapphira wanted. And she was not going to let that happen. <br>
<br>
Knowing that Romans only train with their hands on bare weapons, she knew that without her hands, Sapphira would be incapable of fighting. Alysia drew a dagger and struck it straight through her palm. She screamed in agony. But it was not enough, Alysia took her bloodly hand and held the dagger as firm as she could, but it was no use. She had hurt herself so badly that she couldn't even pick up the hilt. Alysia then dropped the blade and cringed while ripping a piece of cloth from her skirt she wrapped the wound.<br>
